{"updated_at": "2012-04-03T22:51:23Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-04-03T22:51:23Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4938694", "id": 4938694, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5721", "issue_id": 5721, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/glenngillen", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "d72b1e5724b5c20a36d78730b50d8f7b", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/d72b1e5724b5c20a36d78730b50d8f7b?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F630b168462fa22c2e5e80d5175b99ab7.png", "id": 855109, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/events{/privacy}", "login": "glenngillen", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glenngillen/followers"}, "body": "+1 for dependable precedence.\r\n+1 for DATABASE_URL being that precedence for precisely the reasons you point out, it means if someone accidentally commits database.yml then the environment is capable of overriding it with the correct settings.\r\n\r\nI don't think implementation details of the Heroku platform should be dictating design decisions here, we should opt for the most sensible solution. To me that is to give each environment the ability to override database.yml with it's own environment config. It shouldn't blow up if database.yml is missing though.\r\n\r\nGreat catch. And thanks.\r\n\r\nGlenn", "_id": {"$oid": "523813aabd3543c15100dae6"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5721#issuecomment-4938694"}
